marginalia.translation:
It is proper for the excellent, practical man to be knowledgable in theory and industrious in practice;
to be subtle in dubious situations; to be profound in abstruse things; to be careful in secret matters;
to be strong in difficulties; to be constant in toils; to be brilliant in adversity; to be spotless in prosperity;
to be exceptional in singular matters; to be magnificent in everything; and, as often as he requires things
and his skill is sufficient, to be admirable in the majority of his words and deeds.
Needed for the golden art of Chrysotechnus' decorum.
